Secondly.  I, as PoAmae, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> don't feel bad about what happened.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Yes, a few words were said that stung.  But no more than that.  My eyes are clear, I have NEVER taken this into IRL feelings.  I still like and respect PoApep as a friend, though I think because of this my chances of continuing that friendship has been completely thrown out the window.<br>
<br>
Whatever hurt I might have felt has <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>nothing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to do with my age.  Pardon me for saying so, but <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>that</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> really does hurt.  I have prided myself on being mature, emotionally older than my age.  Would you have said the same thing if I were ten years older?  If I were one of the famous roleplayers such as Isharra, Didi, or Sarhea?  I doubt that.  Yes, I'm seventeen.  My age has <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>nothing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to do with my maturity.  <br>
<br>
If you're going to blame me for being a slave, that's your own choice.  Perhaps I'm reading into this too much, but <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>stop belittling me for my RP choices</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I chose to be a slave to Apep back in September.  RP-wise, that is probably the best thing that has happened to me in EQ.  It led to a LOT of really fun RP experiences, such as being trusted by the Dark folk and getting to know them.<br>
<br>
I left Saga for Ebon Storm.  Maybe that still hurts.  If so, I'm sorry, now <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>drop it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  That argument is dead and rotting.<br>
<br>
Stop with your insults on PoApep's manhood and spine.  He has both.  His threats were to the good of roleplaying, and I respect him for that.<br>
<br>
So.  Here's my big secret.  When PoApep and I talked about this, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>did</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> make a huge mistake.  I took his threats on Amae &amp; Co. too seriously.  I took his belief that he could destroy other guilds the way he did Tinker's Pride too seriously.  <br>
<br>
Because I felt that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> should be the one to pay for my transgression, I asked that he rewind in his RP forum, during a thread where he offered Amae her freedom, to change the &quot;No, I'll stay with you&quot; to &quot;Yes, set me free.&quot;  I had two justifications for this.  Firstly, the last post or conversation that had <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>anything</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to do with Amae's freedom was my saying that I'd stay as a slave.  Thus, it wouldn't affect the future which had been, at the time, unwritten.  <br>
<br>
Secondly.  I do NOT like screwing with people OOCly.  I knew there would be hurt ICly because of my leaving the Light side, and I was willing to take that.  Some people took it far too OOCly, and while that still frustrates me, it taught me something.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Never do anything so drastic that people will be cold to you OOCly because of what you did in-game.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  So, I asked that things be changed so that OTHERS would not be hurt by this.  I wanted the blame, I wanted the punishment <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>for myself, as the transgressor, alone</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  OOCly, yes, this was a punishment as well, as some of my best memories of EQ have been ones during my enslavement period.  My relationship to Apep and to PoApep was important to me, but not so much as my want <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not to hurt people OOCly.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  My rule first and foremost, and screw what I think or I feel.<br>
<br>
That's my big secret.  That's what led PoApep to stop respecting me as a roleplayer.  You decide whether you think that's enough.  When he said that his respect for me was deteriorating because of that suggestion, I reconsidered.  Yes I owed more to the story than that.  I was willing to go through with it in the end.  PoApep, because you didn't want to &quot;waste your time&quot; following through with this - which can be understood either as you honestly didn't want to hurt me, because you're justifably too busy with guild and character to bother with the story of one little slave, or because you're tired of people being up your ass because yoyu're one of the few people on this server who dares to roleplay large-scale destruction - that is the only frustration I feel towards you.<br>
